nwawsoft.util

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • nwawsoft.util.Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    Graph data structure. A Graph can contain none to infinitely many GraphNode objects with or without edges between them, which again can be either weighted ur unweighted.

    • Constructor Summary

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if the Graph contains no GraphNode objects. Else false.

      • addNode

        public void addNode(GraphNode graphNode)
        Adds the specified GraphNode object to the Graph. If it is null or a GraphNode object with the same name exists in the Graph already it is not added.
        Parameters:
        graphNode - the GraphNode object to add to the Graph.

      • contains

        public boolean contains(java.lang.String nodeName)
        Returns whether a GraphNode object with the specified name is in the Graph.
        Parameters:
        nodeName - the name of a GraphNode object.
        Returns:
        true if a GraphNode object with the specified name is in the Graph, else false.

      • contains

        public boolean contains(GraphNode graphNode)
        Returns whether a specified GraphNode object is in the Graph.
        Parameters:
        graphNode - a GraphNode object.
        Returns:
        true if the GraphNode is in the Graph, else false.

      • getNode

        public GraphNode getNode(java.lang.String nodeName)
        Returns the GraphNode object with the specified name. Returns null if there is no such GraphNode in the Graph.
        Parameters:
        nodeName - the name of a GraphNode object.
        Returns:
        the GraphNode object with the specified name or null if not on the Graph.

      • removeNode

        public void removeNode(GraphNode graphNode)
        If graphNode != null and graphNode is in the Graph it and all its edges are removed from the Graph. If graphNode == null or not in the Graph nothing happens.
        Parameters:
        graphNode - the graphNode object to remove from the Graph.

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge(GraphNode graphNode1,
                    GraphNode graphNode2,
                    double weight)
        Adds an edge from graphNode1 to graphNode2 with the specified weight. If an edge from graphNode1 to graphNode2 already exists only its weight is set to the new weight. If any specified GraphNode object is null or not in the Graph, nothing changes.
        Parameters:
        graphNode1 - the GraphNode object to create an edge to graphNode2 from.
        graphNode2 - the GraphNode object to create an edge from graphNode 1 to.
        weight - the weight of the new edge.

      • addBidirectionalEdge

        public void addBidirectionalEdge(GraphNode graphNode1,
                                 GraphNode graphNode2,
                                 double weight)
        Adds an edge from graphNode1 to graphNode2 and from graphNode1 to graphNode2, both with the specified weight. If edges between graphNode1 and graphNode2 already exist only their weight is set to the new weight. If any specified GraphNode object is null or not in the Graph, nothing changes.
        Parameters:
        graphNode1 - the GraphNode object to create an edge to and from graphNode2.
        graphNode2 - the GraphNode object to create an edge to and from graphNode1.
        weight - the weight of the new edges.

      • hasEdge

        public boolean hasEdge(GraphNode graphNode1,
                       GraphNode graphNode2)
        Returns whether there is an edge between the specified GraphNode objects in the Graph. If any GraphNode object is null or not in the Graph the result is always false.
        Parameters:
        graphNode1 - a GraphNode object.
        graphNode2 - another GraphNode object.
        Returns:
        true if edge exists, else false.

      • removeEdge

        public void removeEdge(GraphNode graphNode1,
                       GraphNode graphNode2)
        Removes the edge from graphNode1 to graphNode2 if there was any.
        Parameters:
        graphNode1 - a GraphNode object in the Graph.
        graphNode2 - another GraphNode object in the Graph.

      • removeEdges

        public void removeEdges(GraphNode graphNode1,
                        GraphNode graphNode2)
        Removes both edges between graphNode1 and graphNode2 if there were any.
        Parameters:
        graphNode1 - a GraphNode object in the Graph.
        graphNode2 - another GraphNode object in the Graph.

        graphNode2 - another GraphNode object.
